Title: Proebsting's Law
Description:
This means that while hardware computing horsepower increases at roughly
60%/year, compiler optimizations contribute only 4%.

Title: Security Incident at Our Email Vendor
Description: Recently, an employee of our email vendor, Customer.io, used their access to Customer.io systems to download and share a set of email addresses with an unauthorized third party. Late last night, Customer.io informed us that the data extracted included email addresses that our users and subscribers provided to Unstoppable Domains. Our own systems weren’t impacted as part of this incident, which we understand affected six companies.
